notification laws, examining the potent forces driving their rapid nationwide proliferation in the 1990s through today, as well as exploring how the laws have affected the nation's law, society, and governance. In doing so, the book provides compelling insights into the manifold ways in which registration and notification reflect and influence life in modern America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCriminal lawxUnited States. 0aCriminal recordsxUnited States. 0aCriminal recordszUnited States. 7aLAW / Criminal Law / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804771399zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804771399423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804771399.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles